HEADWORD: Sauria
<hw>Sau"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ a lizard.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Reptilia
formerly established to include the Lacertilia, Crocodilia, Dinosauria,
and other groups. By some writers the name is restricted to the
Lacertilia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

